rComments: Like others have said, very passionate about the subject but sometimes hard to follow. I found the tests and exams to be extremely difficult, but I wonder if that is because French is my second language  so it was harder for me to catch the trick questions (of which there are many). Maybe not the course to take if you are not francophone.

Don't take it as an elective, it will ruin you. Talks really fast and is kind of all over the place which makes it hard to take notes. But I have to say she is a really nice person and is super sweet, was just really not for me.

Great prof! Important to show up/listen to class because a lot of the content isn't in the notes, but if you show up and listen juste a little bit you will do great in this class. Both midterm and final were multiple questions and fairly easy.

Honnêtement la meilleure professeure que j'ai eu à l'Université. Ses cours sont vraiment intéressants et elle est super passionée par sa matière, ce qui rend le tout captivant. Elle a un don fou pour l'enseignement. Il y a quand même beaucoup de matière, mais tous les chapitres sont liés entre eux de sorte à former une sorte d'histoire !

Prof Houle is a great professor who is passionate and caring. This class only had a mid term and final exam. For online exams, she does use Respondus Lockdown but is very open to letting us know that we can have access to a "cheat sheet" or our notes if we wish.

My witchcraft class has been the most interesting class I've attended so far. I never dreaded going to class, she is very passionate about the topic and it definitely translates in her teaching. Be careful, the exams are very heavily weighted. I found the course content so captivating that studying was no problem. Take the class!!

such a fantastic teacher, she really cares for students and is passionate about teaching. this class only had a midterm and a final so it wasn't too demanding.. It's a great bird course to get your average up!
This course is considered a bird course for a good reason. Either way, this prof was solid and made sure we had what we needed to succeed.

Solid prof. She's very passionate about what she teaches and makes every class worth going to. Super easy class with one midterm and a final only so I would definitely recommend taking it as an elective. Great prof!
She is very passionate about what she teaches, however, her tests are full of trick questions so you have to study extra hard to get a decent grade.
it was a good class nothing special thou

Really boring classes, she likes to go on tangents bringing up irrelevant topics and stories, I would never take a class with this teacher again made me sick, Sometimes she makes mistakes on the board if you try correcting it she gets mad.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: She was clearly passionate about the subject and it was contagious. She would give lots of small assignments and made sure to come back on topics that seemed to be problematic. Going to class was the highlight of my day, and I will definitely try to take one of her classes again.

She is kind and very enthusiastic about the material, making lectures interesting. although I found the lectures to be interesting, they were very hard to follow. She speaks very quickly at times, making it hard to catch everything she's saying. Her lecturing was all over the place so, taking comprehensible notes was near impossible.

I dont have enough good things to say about Mme Houle! Attending Latin class was the highlight of my week, not only because I enjoyed the subject matter but because she brought so much life to the class. Always very clear about what was expected, gave enough homework to keep us practicing, but not so much that it felt like a chore.

Excellent prof. Clearly loves her field, and classes are always good-interesting. Very approachable and understanding. The lectures were at one end of campus, and she always finished a few minutes early, I'd assume to help anyone who had to rush off to another class at the other end of campus. Assignments were reasonably easy, without being dull.

That was my first CLA class and Mme Houle made it really pleasent. If you put some effort you'll do great. She makes things really interesting and makes sure no one fails the class as she cares so much about her student.

She is one of the best professors at the University. I know this has been said over and over but she taught us about demons and gave us halloween candy! She is obviously so passionate about the subject she teaches and is great to talk to outside of class. Take her class and you will glad you did.

Her love for the topic is contagious. Shes passionate and actually cares about her lectures. Brilliant woman. If you don't know on what to write your essay, she will help you find a subject. And if your lost she will recommend you a book that will always help you in your work (as if she read them all). Take her classes.

She's the best professor I've ever had! Great lectures, cares for her student. Loves questions and actually answers them!! Knows her stuff and is so passionate a 3hour lecture feels like nothing. And she gave us candy during our midterm.

La meilleure professeure que j'ai eu à l'Université d'Ottawa! Elle rend tout super intéressant et elle est passionné par ce qu'elle enseigne. Elle est très juste dans ces examens, si vous allez au cours et que vous écoutez, vous n'allez avoir aucun problème à avoir de très bon résultat. Je vous conseille fortement de prendre ces cours!

Prof Houle is super great for a younger professor. She bases her courses off of Prof. Greatrex's teaching style (power points, longer lectures, term paper and tests with MANY options to them). Show up to class and take extra notes even though she posts much of her info online. Would take a class with her again !!
